1. Install sbt
--------------

See http://www.scala-sbt.org/download.html for instructions.

2. Compile
----------

Run

sbt compile

from the command line. This may take a while as dependencies have to be fetched.

3. Run
------

You can now run Harrsh via sbt (note the "" around the arguments)

sbt "run --tasks examples/basic-benchmarks.bms"

4. Update
---------

To update to a newer revision, run

git pull
sbt clean
sbt compile